This paper is about dialogue act recognition, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes a hierarchical model based on self-attention, which is a popular technique in deep learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves analyzing the effect of dialog length and context padding length, which relates to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the visualization of attention weights, which is a common technique in information retrieval and visualization (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses two datasets, Switchboard Dialogue Act and DailyDialog, which are commonly used in NLP research and evaluation (cs.SD).
